# 5. 熱は、きっと

MEIKO: Okay, here's your Viennese coffee refill.
KAITO: Thank you! Mmm... This smells delicious! You really do make the best coffee in the world, MEIKO!
MEIKO: I know what you're doing. No amount of praise is getting you any ice cream today.
KAITO: What?! H-Haha. I was just giving you my honest opinion...
Akito: Hey.
KAITO: Ah, Akito! Welcome!
MEIKO: Oh, are you by yourself today? We figured that you'd all come over together since we heard that you'd be participating in an event today.
Akito: Yeah, about that... I came to practice on my own after we split in the evening.
KAITO: Really?! You're going to practice?! Right after an event?! Your work ethic really is admirable, Akito.
KAITO: Between the walls in SEKAI coming down and the tree in the plaza growing bigger, quite a lot has been happening recently...
KAITO: These changes must be happening because of the passion you and the others possess! I'm really looking forward to seeing what happens next!
Akito: Passion...
MEIKO: Akito?
Akito: Oh, don't mind me...
KAITO: Did something happen...?
Akito: ... Nothing major happened. It's just...
KAITO: Why don't you tell me what's on your mind?!
Akito: No, again...
KAITO: You don't have to tell me if you're not comfortable, but it might feel good to get things off your chest. I mean, we've been through this before, haven't we?
KAITO: So, why don't you tell me all about what's bothering you?
Akito: Alright... Then, if you don't mind listening for a second...
KAITO: Of course!
KAITO: I see... You're not feeling as driven as before...
Akito: My brain knows that I need to keep doing what I can to reach our next goal.
Akito: But it's like my heart isn't keeping up with it...
MEIKO: Akito...
MEIKO: I don't think there's any reason for you to be feeling so anxious.
Akito: Huh?
MEIKO: You've been doing absolutely everything you can to make a very big dream come true, right?
MEIKO: Your heart may be telling you that it needs some time to recharge right now.
Akito: Yeah, that also crossed my mind...
MEIKO: Also, from where I'm standing, it seems only natural that you're not chasing this new dream with the same amount of fervor as before.
KAITO: Wait, why's that?
MEIKO: Because his dream of surpassing RAD WEEKEND was born out of actually witnessing that event. Seeing it is what inspired him, no?
MEIKO: But he and the others are now trying to “stand on top of the world”, and I'm not sure they quite know what that means yet.
MEIKO: This dream was born under far different circumstances. So, it seems only natural not to go after it in the same way as before.
Akito: ...
Akito: (I get what MEIKO's saying...)
Akito: (But... That doesn't really explain why I haven't been able to perform at my best lately...)
KAITO: Hmm... Let's say MEIKO's right...
KAITO: If seeing RAD WEEKEND is what lit that fire inside of you all those years ago, then you may just need something to help rekindle that flame, Akito.
Akito: Something to rekindle the flame inside of me...?
Akito: (But what are the odds of me seeing another event or anything like that again...)
KAITO: It may actually be hiding right under your nose.
Akito: Huh?
KAITO: To be fair, I can't really say what that is yet...
KAITO: But you understand how big the world is, yes, Akito?
KAITO: You began dreaming of surpassing RAD WEEKEND after just happening to come across it.
KAITO: So, you might find something else that rekindles the flame inside of you.
KAITO: The world is a big place. It's full of things that we don't know about and opportunities we can't imagine.
KAITO: So, as long as you strive towards your goal of standing on top of the world, I'm sure you'll come across that special something eventually.
Akito: ...
Akito: (The world is a big place, huh...?)
Akito: You might have a point there...
Akito: Which is rare of you, KAITO.
KAITO: What?! Rare?! You must be joking! I'm always trying to give the best advice I can to all of you...
MEIKO: He's saying that because of how you act on a daily basis.
KAITO: No, MEIKO, not you too!
Akito: (I'll come across it eventually, huh...?)
Akito: (Obviously, believing that isn't going to get me out of my current situation. But...)
Akito: (It does beat feeling anxious and running around in circles.)
Akito: (In any case, I just gotta keep moving forward.)
Akito: (Like I've been doing until now.)
